{
  "text": "Perinatal events like umbilical catheterization, thrombophilic states, tumors, and abdominal infection are the main causes of hepatic injury leading to portal hypertension (PH) [CITATION_1] . Children submitted to chemoradiotherapy for Wilms' tumor (WT) could also end in PH caused by portal vein fibrosis [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "72707301",
